        "body": "## Summary\nThis refreshes the old session-reset followup work as a clean branch off current `origin/main`.\n\nThe replacement keeps the original intent:\n- preserve queued followup work across `sessions.reset`\n- rebind queued or in-flight reply work to the replacement session before execution\n- drop stale output when an older run has been superseded by a newer session\n\nIt also folds in the unresolved review feedback from the old PR:\n- queued work now recomputes the canonical transcript path when the replacement session entry does not carry a usable `sessionFile`\n- superseded runs now suppress pending block/tool deliveries instead of only suppressing the final payload, which avoids leaking stale streamed chunks after a reset\n\n## Validation\n- `npx vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.misc.runreplyagent.test.ts -t \"drops output when a run is overtaken by a newer session\"`\n- `npx vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts -t \"rebinds queued followups to the latest session after a reset|drops followup output when the run is superseded by a newer session\"`\n- commit-time `pnpm check` / lint hooks passed during `git commit`\n\n## Contribution Notes\n- AI-assisted: yes (`Codex`)\n- Testing degree: lightly tested\n- Review thread handling: addressed and resolved where applicable before re-requesting review\n",
